Jihohi 18 da D.C. sun goyi bayan kalubalen sabon tsarin neman mafaka
Jihohi 18 da kuma D.C. Columbia sun goyi bayan sabon tsarin doka na Amurka na hana baƙi mafaka ga wadanda ke guduwa daga 'yan bindiga ko kuma tashin hankali na cikin gida.
Jaridar NBC ta ruwaito cewa wakilan jihohi da gundumomi 18 sun mika takardun amincewa da kotu a Washington a ranar Juma'a don tallafawa 'yan gudun hijirar da ke adawa da wannan manufa.
Har yanzu ba a bayyana cikakken sunan shari'ar Grace da Sessions ba, wanda Kungiyar 'Yancin Jama'a ta Amurka ta shigar a watan Agusta game da dokar tarayya.
Ta ce abokan aikinta da 'ya'yanta maza masu aikata laifuka sun yi mata fyade, amma hukumomin Amurka sun ki amincewa da bukatar ta ta neman mafaka a ranar 20 ga watan Yuli.
An tsare ta a Texas.
Lauyoyin jihar da ke goyon bayan Grace sun bayyana El Salvador, Honduras da Guatemala, da ke da yawan masu neman mafaka a Amurka, a matsayin kasashe da ke fama da gungun mutane da kuma tashin hankali a cikin gida.
Sabuwar manufar neman mafaka ta Amurka ta sauya shawarar da majalisar dokoki ta yanke a 2014 inda ta ba wa baƙi da ba su da izini damar neman mafaka domin tserewa daga tashin hankali a cikin gida.
Babban lauyan gundumar Columbia, Karl Racine, ya ce a cikin wata sanarwa da ya fitar a ranar Juma'a, "sabon manufar ta yi watsi da dokokin jihohi, tarayya da na kasa da kasa na shekaru goma sha biyu".
"Dangane da dokar tarayya, duk wani neman mafaka dole ne a yanke shi bisa ga takamaiman gaskiyar da yanayin da ake da'awar, kuma irin wannan dokar ta kasa ta keta ka'idar", in ji wata sanarwa daga kotun abokantaka.
Lauyoyin sun kuma yi jayayya a cikin karar cewa dokar hana baƙi shiga tana cutar da tattalin arzikin Amurka, suna cewa suna iya zama 'yan kasuwa kuma suna "samar da ma'aikata da ake buƙata".
